annotationA: Brahma associated protein 55kD; Transcription coactivator activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: mitotic nuclear division; muscle organ development; chromatin remodeling; mitotic cytokinesis; positive regulation of transcription, DNA-templated; dendrite guidance; DNA repair; dendrite morphogenesis; positive regulation of gene silencing by miRNA; Belongs to the actin family
annotationB: Cullin 4 is the molecular scaffold for the CRL4 E3 ubiquitin ligase complex, which catalyzes the ubiquitylation and subsequent destruction of proteins that function in cell growth and proliferation as well as transcription, replication and repair of the genome; Belongs to the cullin family
